Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.02,1:25:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy the idea of thetorium.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.02,1:25:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The fire breakers.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.02,1:25:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is only an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.02,1:25:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And another spiritual teacher says the world as we see it doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.02,1:25:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So she wants to know if that is true, then what about Mozart and nature and the cathedrals
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.02,1:25:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and God, everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.02,1:25:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that's her question.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.12,1:25:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to understand the sentence and the sense in which it is presented.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.90,1:25:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It says the world of perception is not the real world.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.18,1:25:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence is often disguised.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.50,1:25:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you perceive it as perpendic them the world.
